      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hi, I\u0027ve regrettably had to make an automatic mirror of chromium.googlesource.com/crashpad/crashpad to fuchsia.googlesource.com/third_party/crashpad because the Fuchsia project has tighter constraints on acceptable licenses than Chromium and Crashpad.\n\ncrashpad/third_party/xnu is one of the directories that was flagged as being unacceptably licensed. Initially, I assumed I would just be able to filter that directory out in the copy, but having actually tried it, I see now that compat depends on third_party/xnu/BUILD.gn for all non-mac.\n\nCould you suggest a correct cut point? It looks like the xnu headers are only used on mac/ios right now, but the descriptions allude to a possible different future plan?\n\nI believe ios is separate from mac here; is not-mac meant for ios, or is it genuinely wanted on all platforms?",
